page.title: 06INTERESTING PEOPLE.
page.content:
The late Mr. Dorian Williams O.B.E. lived at Foscott Manor for the past 21 years.Until three years ago he was a Show-Jumping commentator.He was Master of the Hounds and President of the British Horse Society.His Parents founded the Pony Club.Very sadly just over a week after we interviewed him Mr. Williams died.
The famous 45-year-old magician Paul Daniels lives in nearby Water Stratford,and can sometimes be seen in Buckingham shopping.
Mr. Gilbert Cantell has been a figure of local importance for some time, having been a School Governor, for example. He is currently Chairman of the League of Friends of Buckingham Hospital.
